   <br><br>
   <h1>JSP and XML</h1>
   <br>
   <h2>What is the relationship?</h2>
   <br>
</center> 
<font size=4>
<ul>
   <li>Java is cross-platform code, and XML is cross-platform data.</li>
   <li>JSP can be written as valid XML documents (can be considered an XML
       application).</li>
   <li>Just as JSP can produce HTML documents, it can also produce XML
       documents.</li>
   <li>Java already has a large set of XML libraries and tools
       available.</li>
</ul>
</font>
